raw_data.title: Automation Technician
raw_data.description: Installation, commissioning, maintenance and repair of Honeywell Control systems. Performs installation, maintenace or repair services, checkout and start-up of diverse technologies including, HVAC, Fire & Security, Integrated systems and internet based computer systems. Also possess basic project management and engineering skills to engineer and install small jobs and perform close-out tasks to meet customer requirements.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Bachelor's Degree in Mechanical / Electrical Engineering, or equivalent industry related experience. Minimum 2 years desired in one or more disciplines related to mechanical, technical, HVAC, Fire and Security Systems, and/or computer system / networking experience required. Ability to provide technical guidance and support on Honeywell products and services with little or no supervision.
raw_data.required_certifications_or_licenses: Fire Alarm Designers are working towards obtaining NICET Level II, III or IV

raw_data.title: Engineer
raw_data.description: Systems design, analysis, installation and integration with a major emphasis on improving system performance to generate savings in energy, operations, and maintenance costs.  Specifies system components to ensure conformance with engineering design and performance specifications. May perform diagnostics and troubleshoots problems as required to resolve system issues and to provide technical information as required. May perform Project Management functions as required including developing project plans, directing personnel, and developing procedures for testing and commissioning.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: B.S. Degree, Engineering, Mechanical or Electrical or equivalent experience.  Generally 5-7 years application engineering experience including large, complex and target job assignments required. Extensive knowledge of Honeywell and industry standard software. Comprehensive understanding of all existing and current Honeywell offerings and ability to integrate the two. Understanding of state, federal and municipal code requirements for electrical, fire, and safety systems. Extensive knowledge of PC’s, software, networks, internet related technologies.

raw_data.title: Mechanical Technician
raw_data.description: Provide a wide-range of on-call, scheduled preventive maintenance, installation and repair services on HVAC equipment and systems, temperature controls, and energy management systems. Provide proactive preventative maintenance to maintain optimal mechanical system operations to attain desired comfort, safety and operating cost efficiencies.
